OL,7,FOver the weekend, Government sources
OL,8,Findicated that Ms Kendall's reforms
OL,9,Fwould include a "right to try
OL,10,Fguarantee" that would allow disabled
OL,11,Fpeople to enter employment without
OL,12,Frisk of losing their benefits if it
OL,13,Fdid not work out.
OL,15,FBut Conservative shadow work and
OL,16,Fpensions secretary Helen Whately said
OL,17,FLabour was "divided" over welfare and
OL,18,F"cannot deliver the decisive change we
OL,19,Fneed".
